<author><name><![CDATA[Disch]]></name></author>
<updated>2006-04-24T09:53:09-07:00</updated>
<published>2006-04-24T09:53:09-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1417&amp;p=12179#p12179</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1417&amp;p=12179#p12179"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[NSA or p8NES??]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1417&amp;p=12179#p12179"><![CDATA[
The pattern tables (CHR) are at $0000-1FFF in ppu memory.  If you want to write to CHR-RAM, you must write each byte and fill that block.<br /><br />Of course for you to write to CHR-RAM, you must first HAVE CHR-RAM.  99% of the time this means you can't have any CHR-ROM.  Only a handful of boards have both CHR-ROM and RAM, most only have one.  So you're usually stuck with just one or the other.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=33">Disch</a> — Mon Apr 24, 2006 9:53 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
